te_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawgame_okc_mil.py"],"evidence":["Production scripts, generated CSVs, notebook work, and reference docs all live in the repository root.","A developer looking for 'core parsing logic' versus 'finished outputs' has no directory boundary to follow; the same root contains `step2_build_possessions.py`, `wmi_rawseason_2024_25_summary.csv`, `01_setup_and_exploration.ipynb`, and multiple planning markdown files."],"suggestion":"Create a small project structure with separate directories such as `src/` for reusable domain code, `scripts/` for runnable jobs, `data/outputs/` for generated files, and `docs/` for definitions/plans so the filesystem itself communicates ownership.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"flat_research_workspace"},{"dimension":"high_level_elegance","identifier":"workflow_is_split_by_one_off_scripts_not_domain_modules","summary":"Core WMI workflow steps are implemented as isolated scripts instead of a coherent domain package.","related_files":["step2_build_possessions.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py","build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py"],"evidence":["`step2_build_possessions.py`, `categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py`, and `build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py` all reconstruct overlapping play-by-play parsing and possession grouping behavior instead of calling a shared parser module.","`calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py` computes season output by rebuilding possession tables inline, while `calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py` uses a different inline path (`build_foul_vector` and `game_wmi_components`) for the same metric family.","The file names are anchored to specific samples or date ranges (`okc_mil`, `2024_25`, `2010_11_to_2023_24`) rather than stable concepts like parser, possession model, or WMI calculator."],"suggestion":"Extract stable domain modules such as `playbyplay_loader`, `possession_parser`, `foul_classifier`, and `wmi_metrics`, then keep the current files as thin entry-point scripts that wire those pieces together for a game sample or a season run.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"flat_research_workspace"},{"dimension":"high_level_elegance","identifier":"project_docs_do_not_define_a_single_trustworthy_public_surface","summary":"The docs describe the project inconsistently, so the intended entry points and current structure are unclear.","related_files":["README.md","Plan for WMI - Ryan Kalfus (2026).md","Definitions for NBA Analytics Research - Ryan Kalfus (2026).md"],"evidence":["`README.md` only lists the possession builder script and one sample output, which makes the project look like a single-step parser.","`Plan for WMI - Ryan Kalfus (2026).md` says the current implementation includes a one-game prototype plus season scaling and lists several current output files.","`Definitions for NBA Analytics Research - Ryan Kalfus (2026).md` defines additional current files and workflow stages, but none of these docs tells a newcomer which script is the canonical entry point for reproducing the pipeline end to end."],"suggestion":"Replace the scattered top-level project description with one canonical workflow document in `README.md` that states the pipeline stages, the authoritative scripts or commands for each stage, and where reusable code versus generated artifacts live.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"flat_research_workspace"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["The project appears to have grown from exploratory analysis runs, so new capabilities were added as new top-level scripts and output files instead of being folded into a stable module layout.","Documentation is being used as research notes and rule definitions, but not as an arch